{"TopicId":224328,"ForumId":139,"TopicTitle":"[APRIL FOOLS] The Empire Strikes Back: KSP2 Adopts Imperial Units","CreatedByName":"Intercept Games","CreatedById":210281,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:35:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Intercept Games","CreatedById":210281,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:35:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221461\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/image.png.fa48ac2ce9619ceeb6ecec8fa80c0fc7.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221461\u0022 data-ratio=\u002220.92\u0022 data-unique=\u0022v0euqgvph\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/image.thumb.png.182c8fc85d2fe052476a7494193b0d20.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowdy Kerbonauts!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ve got some \u003Cem\u003EBIG KSP2 NEWS\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Ethat\u0027s going to rock your world!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter much deliberation with the development team, fueled by copious amounts of leftover pizza and donuts (thanks Darrin!) we\u0027ve decided to make a Kerbin-shattering decision.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKerbal Space Program 2 is officially transitioning from that new-fangled metric system to the good ol\u0027 IMPERIAL system.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_FlightHUD_V5.png.563b3153d80d3f3844aed8a11addeab0.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_FlightHUD_V5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221457\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 data-unique=\u00220ss7hmj9i\u0022 style=\u0022width: 800px; height: auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_FlightHUD_V5.thumb.png.76bd0b26920f3559af74baf68b716369.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s right - inches, feet, yards, and maybe the occasional nautical mile for your aquatic craft needs!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_Boat_V5.png.a6f9ed0b0a5f8cf62046090cbb2cee87.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_Boat_V5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221456\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 data-unique=\u00224wv463kas\u0022 style=\u0022width: 800px; height: auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_Boat_V5.thumb.png.ea86aed962bcf1b9aa913cc8a3265317.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, hold up - we can hear you typing that comment and getting those downvote bots ready - \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022But WHY Intercept?!?! Metric is loved by scientists worldwide!\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, hold onto your butts, because we have some \u003Cem\u003Estellar \u003C/em\u003Ereasons for this \u003Cem\u003Eastronomical \u003C/em\u003Eshift:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOne, as every space buff knows, the Apollo Guidance Computer was a big fan of the imperial system.\u003C/strong\u003E Sure it did its internal calculations in metric, but what did it display to the astronauts aboard?\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat\u0027s right - IMPERIAL! If it\u0027s good enough to get us to the moon, it\u0027s good enough for the Kerbals. We\u0027re all about that authentic space experience!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_TrackingStation_V5.png.70941854fea4b82c5115696fd2947614.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_TrackingStation_V5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221459\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 data-unique=\u0022fe5e0sjqg\u0022 style=\u0022width: 800px; height: auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_TrackingStation_V5.thumb.png.edf05fbf9f7173d47122a59efc113521.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ETwo - look, we\u0027re American developers. We grew up knowing how long a football field is, not how many meters are in a kilometer.\u003C/strong\u003E We\u0027re still not sure, actually. Plus, who really knows what a \u0022newton\u0022 is? Sounds like a cookie to be honest.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOn the other hand, everyone knows what a pound is - it\u0027s the weight of a hamburger. That\u0027s hard relatable science right there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThree, Imperial is just more fun!\u00A0Have you ever tried saying \u0022kilometer\u0022 five times fast?\u003C/strong\u003E Now try \u0022yard!\u0022 Whew - see way more fun! Plus, \u0022miles per hour\u0022 is totally cooler than \u0022kilometers per hour\u0022 - c\u0027mon it doesn\u0027t even compare.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EFour, everyone likes it when number go up.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Admit it, saying your rocket is 300 feet tall sounds WAY more impressive than a mere 91 meters. 300?!? That\u0027s like a Skyscraper!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, with this switch to imperial, get ready to ditch those pesky decimal points and embrace FRACTIONS!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_VAB_V5.png.e042bdf84a5df8120c0cc13234e454b4.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_VAB_V5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221460\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 data-unique=\u0022hipu70nit\u0022 style=\u0022width: 800px; height: auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_VAB_V5.thumb.png.332c87ff24b78fc333c1c95c6e979a0c.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo more \u0022meters per second,\u0022 we\u0027re now cruising through the Kerbolar system at \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022furlongs per fortnight.\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd fuel measurements? \u003Cstrong\u003EGallons, of course\u003C/strong\u003E. None of that \u0022liters\u0022 stuff. Once we go Interstellar though, we\u0027re using hogsheads.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTemperature? Fahrenheit, because nothing says reentry like a number larger than your average oven temperature.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, we can hear you saying \u0022are you sure this is a good idea? Don\u0027t you remember what happened to the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_Climate_Orbiter\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMars Climate Orbiter\u003C/a\u003E?\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yeah - we do! But ya know, our math skillz are pretty good, so \u003Cstrong\u003Etrust us - we got i\u003C/strong\u003Et \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 loading=\u0022lazy\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E----\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThese changes are included with KSP2 v0.2.1.6.1.3.9.1-3a (final)\u003C/strong\u003E which should arrive to you in only a couple inch-years!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo help everyone adjust, this release will include\u003Cstrong\u003E a virtual tape measure, a new survey part\u003C/strong\u003E for exciting new measuring missions, and \u003Cstrong\u003Ean in-game abacus\u003C/strong\u003E for all of your unit converstion needs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, Keri will be offering some \u003Cstrong\u003Enew missions to help teach imperial units\u003C/strong\u003E to our more metricly-inclined players.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 href=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_MissionControl_V7.png.c92a9fc34278e82107ca70b3238dd3aa.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_MissionControl_V7.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221458\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 data-unique=\u002236jgneioh\u0022 style=\u0022width: 800px; height: auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_MissionControl_V7.thumb.png.b3bef02cf0b410fe501e5e90bbce66b8.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E---\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EWe\u0027re excited to take this next step of Kerbal Space Program 2\u0027s journey and can\u0027t wait for you to embrace the quirks and quandaries of the imperial system with us!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EAnd consider that this is not just a game update; \u003Cstrong\u003Eit\u0027s a historical homage\u003C/strong\u003E - perhaps a tip of the hat - to the days when measurements were as inconsistent as many of your landing attempts.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EWe hope you are looking forward to having\u003Cstrong\u003E bushels of fun\u003C/strong\u003E with this update as we redefine KSP2\u0027s gameplay experience - one pint, pound, and peck at a time.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKSP2 Dev Team\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChadDude","CreatedById":229755,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:47:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need every single type of measurement now in KSP2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stephensan","CreatedById":222320,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:48:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Eyeah really cannot take this as a meme\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E, its been a hot debate recently about adding more than just m/s or m.. and i don\u0027t even want to use imperial\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nkm/h\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nknots\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand imperial units.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nall needs to be added, certain vehicles be much better for km/h like planes and ground vehicles etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsorry, please add more units of measurements..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-gaming community\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-04-01T16:48:29Z\u0022 title=\u002204/01/2024 04:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Apr 1\u0022\u003EApril 1\u003C/time\u003E by Stephensan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ILikeIke","CreatedById":145488,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:52:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d live with it if it meant more frequent dev updates.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:53:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSurprised you\u0027re still measuring time in hours, minutes and seconds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mindseyemodels","CreatedById":177219,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:53:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnironically we need more units of measurements in terms of speed and distance\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pk9sp","CreatedById":229508,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:54:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWHAT THE DONK IS A KILOMETER?!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Little 908","CreatedById":228185,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:54:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfreedom\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/1437623226_rocket_1f680(3).png\u0022 title=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/1437623226_rocket_1f680(3).png\u0022 title=\u0022:1437623226_rocket_1f680(3):\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocketology","CreatedById":152263,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:55:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am happy that today is April Fools Day...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Audaylon","CreatedById":228158,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:58:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery cool.\u00A0 And that sea craft looks amazing.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:58:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DibzNr","CreatedById":212219,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T16:59:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKerbal Freedom Program 2\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drunken Monkey Style","CreatedById":177742,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:00:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs long as all the asteroids are measured in refrigerators and/or giraffes, I\u0027m good.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.forbes.com/sites/jamiecartereurope/2023/01/23/see-the-giraffe-sized-asteroid-found-on-saturday-whizz-scary-close-to-earth-on-thursday/?sh=72b8aadd2a41\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.forbes.com/sites/jamiecartereurope/2023/01/23/see-the-giraffe-sized-asteroid-found-on-saturday-whizz-scary-close-to-earth-on-thursday/?sh=72b8aadd2a41\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2022/03/17/asteroid-hits-earth/7079963001/#:~:text=Fridge-sized%20asteroid%20hit%20Earth%202%20hours%20after,was%20first%20spotted%2C%20NASA%20says\u0026amp;text=An%20asteroid%20around%20the%20size,right%20before%20hitting%20our%20planet.\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2022/03/17/asteroid-hits-earth/7079963001/#:~:text=Fridge-sized asteroid hit Earth 2 hours after,was first spotted%2C NASA says\u0026amp;text=An asteroid around the size,right before hitting our planet.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Orion-CSAT","CreatedById":232283,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:05:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI sincerely hope this isn\u0027t an April fools thing, imperial is actually kinda fun. Honestly, I was sold by the Apollo argument.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tony Tony Chopper","CreatedById":229524,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:08:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEEEHHHH?!\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nOkay you had me for 10 seconds, not gonna lie.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hidearimjosh","CreatedById":226610,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:11:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRAHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E:eagle: :eagle:\u00A0:eagle:\u00A0:eagle:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:13:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224376724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221711989300\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210281\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Intercept Games\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, Intercept Games said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n.2.1.6.1.3.9.1-3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuh\u2026. You\u2019re only missing the last two digits of my phone number. \u00A0 \u00A0Area code and all.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cepheus","CreatedById":10683,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:16:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmissed opprotunity to use the\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eslug\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0for mass. Gotta have all those really weird imperial aerospace units!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dandoesstuff","CreatedById":223454,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:36:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwen release\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-04-01T17:36:57Z\u0022 title=\u002204/01/2024 05:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Apr 1\u0022\u003EApril 1\u003C/time\u003E by dandoesstuff\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CatastrophicFailure","CreatedById":57438,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:37:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00220KvTiQe.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.56\u0022 height=\u0022406\u0022 width=\u0022610\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/0KvTiQe.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:37:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone needs to put a foot\u00A0down. Everyday we inch closer to madness. We will knot stand for this!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flush Foot","CreatedById":193460,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:37:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224376785\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221711993020\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257438\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CatastrophicFailure\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, CatastrophicFailure said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/0KvTiQe.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00220KvTiQe.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.56\u0022 height=\u0022406\u0022 width=\u0022610\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/0KvTiQe.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\u00A0(Kerbal agrees)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dandoesstuff","CreatedById":223454,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:39:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224376787\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221711993055\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224498\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Space Peacock\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, The Space Peacock said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone needs to put a foot\u00A0down. Everyday we inch closer to madness. We will knot stand for this!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou\u0027re miles ahead\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nor something like that i can\u0027t figure out a good pun\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:40:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224376724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221711989300\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210281\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Intercept Games\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Intercept Games said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221461\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/image.png.fa48ac2ce9619ceeb6ecec8fa80c0fc7.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221461\u0022 data-ratio=\u002220.92\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/image.thumb.png.182c8fc85d2fe052476a7494193b0d20.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowdy Kerbonauts!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ve got some \u003Cem\u003EBIG KSP2 NEWS\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Ethat\u0027s going to rock your world!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter much deliberation with the development team, fueled by copious amounts of leftover pizza and donuts (thanks Darrin!) we\u0027ve decided to make a Kerbin-shattering decision.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKerbal Space Program 2 is officially transitioning from that new-fangled metric system to the good ol\u0027 IMPERIAL system.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221457\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_FlightHUD_V5.png.563b3153d80d3f3844aed8a11addeab0.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_FlightHUD_V5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221457\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_FlightHUD_V5.thumb.png.76bd0b26920f3559af74baf68b716369.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s right - inches, feet, yards, and maybe the occasional nautical mile for your aquatic craft needs!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221456\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_Boat_V5.png.a6f9ed0b0a5f8cf62046090cbb2cee87.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_Boat_V5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221456\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_Boat_V5.thumb.png.ea86aed962bcf1b9aa913cc8a3265317.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, hold up - we can hear you typing that comment and getting those downvote bots ready - \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022But WHY Intercept?!?! Metric is loved by scientists worldwide!\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, hold onto your butts, because we have some \u003Cem\u003Estellar \u003C/em\u003Ereasons for this \u003Cem\u003Eastronomical \u003C/em\u003Eshift:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOne, as every space buff knows, the Apollo Guidance Computer was a big fan of the imperial system.\u003C/strong\u003E Sure it did its internal calculations in metric, but what did it display to the astronauts aboard?\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat\u0027s right - IMPERIAL! If it\u0027s good enough to get us to the moon, it\u0027s good enough for the Kerbals. We\u0027re all about that authentic space experience!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221459\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_TrackingStation_V5.png.70941854fea4b82c5115696fd2947614.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_TrackingStation_V5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221459\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_TrackingStation_V5.thumb.png.edf05fbf9f7173d47122a59efc113521.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ETwo - look, we\u0027re American developers. We grew up knowing how long a football field is, not how many meters are in a kilometer.\u003C/strong\u003E We\u0027re still not sure, actually. Plus, who really knows what a \u0022newton\u0022 is? Sounds like a cookie to be honest.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOn the other hand, everyone knows what a pound is - it\u0027s the weight of a hamburger. That\u0027s hard relatable science right there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThree, Imperial is just more fun!\u00A0Have you ever tried saying \u0022kilometer\u0022 five times fast?\u003C/strong\u003E Now try \u0022yard!\u0022 Whew - see way more fun! Plus, \u0022miles per hour\u0022 is totally cooler than \u0022kilometers per hour\u0022 - c\u0027mon it doesn\u0027t even compare.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EFour, everyone likes it when number go up.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Admit it, saying your rocket is 300 feet tall sounds WAY more impressive than a mere 91 meters. 300?!? That\u0027s like a Skyscraper!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, with this switch to imperial, get ready to ditch those pesky decimal points and embrace FRACTIONS!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221460\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_VAB_V5.png.e042bdf84a5df8120c0cc13234e454b4.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_VAB_V5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221460\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_VAB_V5.thumb.png.332c87ff24b78fc333c1c95c6e979a0c.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo more \u0022meters per second,\u0022 we\u0027re now cruising through the Kerbolar system at \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022furlongs per fortnight.\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd fuel measurements? \u003Cstrong\u003EGallons, of course\u003C/strong\u003E. None of that \u0022liters\u0022 stuff. Once we go Interstellar though, we\u0027re using hogsheads.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTemperature? Fahrenheit, because nothing says reentry like a number larger than your average oven temperature.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, we can hear you saying \u0022are you sure this is a good idea? Don\u0027t you remember what happened to the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mars_Climate_Orbiter\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMars Climate Orbiter\u003C/a\u003E?\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yeah - we do! But ya know, our math skillz are pretty good, so \u003Cstrong\u003Etrust us - we got i\u003C/strong\u003Et \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E----\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThese changes are included with KSP2 v0.2.1.6.1.3.9.1-3a (final)\u003C/strong\u003E which should arrive to you in only a couple inch-years!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo help everyone adjust, this release will include\u003Cstrong\u003E a virtual tape measure, a new survey part\u003C/strong\u003E for exciting new measuring missions, and \u003Cstrong\u003Ean in-game abacus\u003C/strong\u003E for all of your unit converstion needs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, Keri will be offering some \u003Cstrong\u003Enew missions to help teach imperial units\u003C/strong\u003E to our more metricly-inclined players.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221458\u0022 href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_MissionControl_V7.png.c92a9fc34278e82107ca70b3238dd3aa.png\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Imperial_MissionControl_V7.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221458\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.38\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/Imperial_MissionControl_V7.thumb.png.b3bef02cf0b410fe501e5e90bbce66b8.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E---\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EWe\u0027re excited to take this next step of Kerbal Space Program 2\u0027s journey and can\u0027t wait for you to embrace the quirks and quandaries of the imperial system with us!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EAnd consider that this is not just a game update; \u003Cstrong\u003Eit\u0027s a historical homage\u003C/strong\u003E - perhaps a tip of the hat - to the days when measurements were as inconsistent as many of your landing attempts.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EWe hope you are looking forward to having\u003Cstrong\u003E bushels of fun\u003C/strong\u003E with this update as we redefine KSP2\u0027s gameplay experience - one pint, pound, and peck at a time.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKSP2 Dev Team\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Forehead-Slap.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.15\u0022 height=\u0022172\u0022 width=\u0022260\u0022 src=\u0022https://blogherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/Forehead-Slap.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Flush Foot","CreatedById":193460,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-01T17:56:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224376790\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022224328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221711993162\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223454\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dandoesstuff\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, dandoesstuff said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou\u0027re miles ahead\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nor something like that i can\u0027t figure out a good pun\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know we all \u003Cstrike\u003Eneed to\u003C/strike\u003E want the devs to touch grass (in the yard) but that doesn\u2019t mean we wanted to switch from logical units to freedumb units!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}